# Vallejo Design System Rules for Cursor

Use **Vallejo only** when building UI for [Copart.com](https://www.copart.com). Do not use Tailwind, Bootstrap, or other design systems for Copart.com — use Vallejo so output matches production.

**Essential references (priority order):**
- `SYSTEM-INDEX.json` — system map and file locations (start here for navigation)
- `LLM-ACCESS-GUIDE.md` — efficient navigation guide for LLMs
- `NEW-AGENT-PROMPT.md` — full handoff; start new agents here
- `AI-QUICK-REFERENCE.md` — component classes and HTML patterns (use first for implementation)
- `CURSOR-PROMPT.md` — implementation strategy, accessibility, troubleshooting
- `LAYOUT-PATTERNS.md` — Copart.com patterns (listings, dashboard, bid modal, search)
- `components/catalog.json` — Figma node IDs, `componentClasses`
- `tokens/` + `tokens/README.md` — design tokens and hierarchy

**Figma:** File key `ixkN3RSoiQc5aSlxZ21Hay`. Node IDs in `catalog.json`.

**Rules:** Use exact class names from AI-QUICK-REFERENCE; use design tokens (CSS variables); check `docs/design-system-guide.md` for "When to use" and anti-patterns when choosing components. Default to `test-examples/all-components-demo.html` for implementation.
